      "Your video description should be at least 200 words long and include your primary keyword in the first two sentences. Provide a genuine summary of the video content, include timestamps for different sections, and add relevant links.",
      "## 4. Use Tags Strategically",
      "While tags are less influential than they once were, they still help YouTube understand your content. Use your exact target keyword as the first tag, followed by variations and related terms. Include both broad and specific tags for comprehensive coverage.",
      "## 5. Optimize Your Thumbnail",
      "A compelling thumbnail directly impacts your CTR, which influences rankings. Use bright, contrasting colors, include readable text, and feature faces when possible. Custom thumbnails consistently outperform auto-generated ones.",
      "## 6. Add Closed Captions",
      "Accurate closed captions provide YouTube with a complete text version of your content, improving its ability to understand and rank your video. Upload custom captions rather than relying solely on auto-generated ones for better accuracy.",
      "## 7. Create Engaging Content",
      "No amount of optimization can overcome poor content. Create videos that genuinely help, entertain, or inform your viewers. High watch time and engagement signals are the strongest ranking factors.",
